Uses of Package
com.vmware.vcenter.storage

  • Packages that use com.vmware.vcenter.storage 
    Package Description
    com.vmware.vcenter
    The com.vmware.vcenter package provides interfaces for managing VMware vSphere environments.
    com.vmware.vcenter.storage  
  • Classes in com.vmware.vcenter.storage used by com.vmware.vcenter 
    Class and Description
    StorageFactory
    StorageFactory is responsible for creating instances of services contained inside the com.vmware.vcenter.storage package and also has the subpackages reference to access respective subpackage services.
  • Classes in com.vmware.vcenter.storage used by com.vmware.vcenter.storage 
    Class and Description
    Policies
    The Policies interface provides methods for managing the storage policies.
    Policies.CheckCompatibilityInvocation
    Invocable that represents the Policies#checkCompatibility vAPI operation.
    Policies.ListInvocation
    Invocable that represents the Policies#list vAPI operation.
    PoliciesTypes
    The Policies interface provides methods for managing the storage policies.
    PoliciesTypes.CompatibilityInfo
    The CompatibilityInfo class contains info about a list of datastores compatible with a specific storage policy.
    PoliciesTypes.CompatibleDatastoreInfo
    The CompatibleDatastoreInfo class contains compatible datastore's information.
    PoliciesTypes.FilterSpec
    The FilterSpec class contains properties used to filter the results when listing the storage policies (see Policies.list()).
    PoliciesTypes.FilterSpec.Builder
    Builder class for PoliciesTypes.FilterSpec.
    PoliciesTypes.Summary
    The Summary class contains commonly used information about a storage policy.
    StorageFactory
    StorageFactory is responsible for creating instances of services contained inside the com.vmware.vcenter.storage package and also has the subpackages reference to access respective subpackage services.
